Chelsea Brazillian winger, Willian has joined FA Cup holders, Arsenal on a three-year deal. Arsenal announced the new signing via its Twitter handle on Friday. The 32-year-old left Stamford Bridge after seven years with Chelsea only willing to offer him a two-year deal. Arsenal moved into pole position to sign the Brazil international by offering a three-year contract last week. Willian made 47 appearances for Chelsea in all competitions and finished the season in fine form, with four Premier League goals after the restart taking his tally for the season to nine.